## Problem

Task 6 added a wipe call at the end of `@ax/credentials` `init()`. It calls `bus.call('storage:get', ...)` directly. But several downstream test harnesses (notably `@ax/auth-better` admin-routes.test.ts and hot-reload.test.ts) stub only the `credentials:store-blob:*` hooks — they don't provide `storage:get/set/delete-prefix`. So init blows up with `no plugin registered for service hook 'storage:get'`, breaking 12 tests.

## Fix

In `packages/credentials/src/plugin.ts`, gate the wipe call on `bus.hasService('storage:get')`. If the storage layer isn't available, the wipe is a no-op — there's nothing to wipe in a test harness with no persistence.

The pattern to use (matches the existing pattern in `@ax/agents` deleteAgent, plan Task 17):

```ts
if (bus.hasService('storage:get')) {
  const wipeCtx = makeAgentContext({
    sessionId: 'credentials-wipe', agentId: PLUGIN_NAME, userId: 'system',
  });
  await wipePreRedesignCredentials(bus, wipeCtx);
}
```

First, **verify `bus.hasService` exists** on `HookBus`. Read `packages/core/src/hook-bus.ts` (or wherever HookBus lives) and confirm the method name. If it's spelled differently (e.g. `hasRegisteredService`, `serviceExists`), use the actual name.

If no such method exists, fall back to a try/catch:

```ts
try {
  await wipePreRedesignCredentials(bus, wipeCtx);
} catch (err) {
  // Storage isn't wired in this harness; nothing to wipe.
  if (!(err instanceof Error) || !err.message.includes("no plugin registered for service hook")) {
    throw err;
  }
}
```

Prefer the `hasService` shape if it exists — explicit > catch-and-sniff.

## Verify

```bash
